g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: whenever odg-activate-interfaces-at-startup receives a value and when odg-activate-interfaces-at-startup is false then deactivate the subworkspace of odg-INTERFACES-GOTo
whenever odg-activate-interfaces-at-startup receives a value and when odg-activate-interfaces-at-startup is true then activate the subworkspace of odg-INTERFACES-GOTo

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Deactivate Interfaces WS
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: deactivate the subworkspace of odg-INTERFACES-GOTo and conclude that odg-activate-interfaces-at-startup = false

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Activate Interfaces WS
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: activate the subworkspace of odg-INTERFACES-GOTo and conclude that odg-activate-interfaces-at-startup = true

g2:c.READOUT-TABLE.g2:a.EXPRESSION-TO-DISPLAY: the text of the notes of the subworkspace of odg-interfaces-goto

g2:c.KB-WORKSPACE.g2:a.TITLE-BAR-TEXT: ODG-CORE ODG Interfaces and associated logic

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: for any odg-rediscovery-configuration R unconditionally start SCHEDULE-REDISCOVERY (R)

for any opfo-domain-object O whenever the _opfo-highest-message-priority of O receives a value and when the _opfo-highest-message-priority of O/= 99999 and the _juuid of O /= "" then start odg-fire-attribute-change-event (O, "_opfo-highest-message-priority", "[the _opfo-highest-message-priority of O ]")
whenever the opfo-external-name of any opfo-domain-object X receives a value and when the _juuid of X /= "" and the _juuid of X /= the opfo-external-name of X then start ODGS-NAME-Change(X)
whenever the gsi-interface-status of odg-interface receives a value and when the gsi-interface-status of odg-interface = -2 then start odg-reset-interface(odg-interface)

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: Interface Rules and logic (ODG-CORE)

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: REDISCOVER
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: start odgs-start-rediscovery ( the opfo-external-name of the item)

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: DELETE-FROM-ATTRIBUTE-LIST
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: the text of the gsi-interface-status of odg-interface = "2"

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: ADD-TO-ATTRIBUTE-LIST
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: the text of the gsi-interface-status of odg-interface = "2"

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: The gateway is to map NetSleuth class.attributes as specified to Integrity.

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: REMOVE-FROM-IGNORE-LIST
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: the text of the gsi-interface-status of odg-interface = "2"
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: start odgs-remove-ignored-class (the dxi3-type-string of the item)

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: ADD-TO-IGNORE-LIST
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: the text of the gsi-interface-status of odg-interface = "2"
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: start odgs-add-ignored-class (the dxi3-type-string of the item)

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: The gateway is to ignore objects indicated by odg-ignore-class-object configuration items.

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: HIDE-THIS-WORKSPACE
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: hide the workspace of the item on this window

c.DEVU-SCALAR-INITIALIZATION.ua.DEVU-DESCRIPTION: Indicates if starting KB causes Autodiscovery model to be downloaded. If KB is saved with complete domain model, this should be false; if KB has no model objects, this should be true.

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: The ODG-CONVERT-PRIORITY method converts opfo-domain-object priorities to NetSleuth priorities which have desired colors. To change the mapping, create, in your application, a new method on the opfo-domain-object class.

c.DEVU-GSI-INTERFACE-INITIALIZATION.ua.DEVU-DESCRIPTION: ODG Bridge. Configure where the java component can be found.

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: whenever the dxi3-translation-workspace W of odg-import-object receives a value and when there exists a kb-workspace W2 named by W and there exists a dxi3-type-to-class-object D upon W2 such that (the dxi3-type-string of D = "com.gensym.nm.model.UnknownInterface") then conclude that odg-unknown-interface-class = the dxi3-type-class of D

whenever the dxi3-translation-workspace W of odg-import-object receives a value and when there exists a kb-workspace W2 named by W and there exists a dxi3-type-to-class-object D upon W2 such that (the dxi3-type-string of D = "com.gensym.nm.model.UnspecifiedIPDevice") then conclude that odg-unspecified-device-class = the dxi3-type-class of D

c.DEVU-SCALAR-INITIALIZATION.ua.DEVU-DESCRIPTION: Indicates if ODG processing should be active or not.
